  "summary": "Main\nThe market is broadly flat week on week, with the Baltic spot indexes showing limited short-term movement, but remain clearly elevated compared with pre-Christmas levels. The headline rate moved up 1.6% on last week but up 16.9% compared to 24 December. China to West Coast USA FBX01 was up 4.9% on the week and 28.6% on Christmas and China to East Coast was up 5% and 17.3%, respectively.",
